HONORHALL ORPHANAGE: THE SAINT AND THE FACTORY
Standalone Investigation Module ΓÇö Riften City Party Tier: Expert (AP 10) | Estimated Runtime: 1-2 hours Primary PC: Orion | Secondary: Any party member who assists

MODULE DASHBOARD
Function: Orion must investigate, infiltrate, and assassinate Grelod the Kind ΓÇö the most beloved woman in Riften, who is secretly a child-abusing monster running a Thieves Guild training pipeline. He must also enthrall Constance Michel for either Valerius or himself. The module provides the setup, the evidence, and the complications. The execution is entirely player-driven.
This is NOT a dungeon. It is a social investigation with an infiltration component. There are no combat encounters unless Orion creates them. The challenge is informational (discovering Grelod's true nature), social (navigating the city's adoration of her), logistical (getting in, killing her, getting out), and moral (what happens to the children, the pipeline, and Constance).
The Four Masters: Orion must satisfy or betray four competing demands:
Aventus Aretino (Brotherhood client): Grelod suffers. The children know they are free.
Maven Black-Briar: The pipeline continues. Constance takes over. No disruption.
Valerius Caelus (via the Ring): Constance is enthralled through the Ring. She becomes the Court's asset.
Orion himself: Does he obey Valerius, or does he use his own power to enthrall Constance for himself?
Timeline: The contract gives Orion a fortnight. There is no mechanical timer. The pressure is narrative ΓÇö every day he delays, the children suffer another day under Grelod.

THE PUBLIC FACE: CITY VIGNETTES
These are scripted moments the GM drops during normal city exploration ΓÇö BEFORE Orion enters the orphanage. They establish Grelod's public persona. Space them across the party's time in Riften. Each one makes the assassination harder to justify in public.
VIGNETTE 1: THE MARKET SAINT
When: The party's first visit to the Riften market.
Read aloud: "As you browse the market stalls, you notice the crowd part with warm murmurs. A small, elderly woman in a simple grey dress moves through the market with a wicker basket over her arm. Her hair is white, pinned beneath a modest cap. Her face is lined and kind ΓÇö the face of someone's grandmother.
Every merchant she passes greets her by name. 'Mother Grelod!' Madesi calls, pressing a small silver pendant into her hand. 'For the children. Please.' She protests ΓÇö 'Oh, you are too generous, dear' ΓÇö but accepts with a gentle smile. Balimund waves her over and hands her a bundle wrapped in cloth. 'New blankets. The nights are getting cold.' She touches his arm. 'Kynareth bless you, Balimund. The little ones will sleep warm tonight because of you.'
A guard tips his helmet as she passes. A child from the street ΓÇö not an orphan, a merchant's daughter ΓÇö runs up and hugs her legs. Grelod laughs, bends down with visible effort, and smooths the girl's hair. 'Be good for your mother, little one.'
She moves on toward the orphanage, basket full of donated goods, trailing warmth like a wake."
What Orion sees: His target. A tiny old woman the entire city loves. Killing her publicly would be suicide. Killing her at all will devastate this community.
VIGNETTE 2: THE MEMORIAL SPEECH
When: Near the canal memorial, the day after the party arrives.
Read aloud: "A small crowd has gathered near the plague memorial. Grelod stands at its base, speaking. Her voice is thin but carries.
'We lost good people. Mothers. Fathers. Children who never had the chance to grow. But we are still here. Riften endures because we care for each other ΓÇö because when the darkness came, we did not hide. We opened our doors. We shared our bread. We held each other.'
She pauses. Her eyes are wet.
'The orphanage took in six new children during the plague. Six little souls who lost everything. And do you know what they told me? They said they were scared. And I told them what I tell every child who comes through my door: You are safe now. You are loved. And you will never be alone again.'
The crowd applauds. A woman wipes her eyes. A man places flowers at the memorial. Grelod accepts embraces from three separate people before she can make it back to the orphanage."
What Orion sees: The contract says "the children know they are free." These people think the children already ARE free. They think Grelod IS freedom.
VIGNETTE 3: THE PRIVATE CRUELTY (Only if Orion observes the orphanage)
When: Orion watches the orphanage from the canal after dark. Guile TN 14 to approach unseen.
Read aloud: "The orphanage goes dark early. By the ninth bell, the candles in the main hall are extinguished. But a light burns on the upper floor ΓÇö Grelod's quarters.
Through the window you see a different woman. The grandmother is gone. Grelod sits at a desk, reviewing a ledger with the cold focus of a quartermaster. A boy ΓÇö maybe ten ΓÇö stands before her. He is holding his hands out, palms up. On each palm sits a heavy book. His arms are trembling.
Grelod does not look up from the ledger. She speaks without raising her voice, and even through the glass you can hear the ice in it:
'Your hands are shaking, Hroar. A pickpocket with shaking hands is a pickpocket who gets caught. And a pickpocket who gets caught is worthless to me. Worthless children do not eat breakfast. Begin again. And this time, hold them steady, or you hold them until morning.'
The boy's lip trembles. He adjusts his grip. The books wobble. Grelod still does not look up."
What Orion sees: The truth. The grandmother is a mask. Underneath is something methodical, patient, and cruel.

